PeakWidth over RT

This plot shows the variation of peak width over the RT dimension.
The data for these plots was taken from OpenSwathWorkflow output:
  • FKL2872-S02-A-A_DIA_stepCE_1.osw
  • FKL2872-S10-A-A_DIA_stepCE_2.osw
  • FKL2872-S14-A-A_DIA_stepCE_3.osw
  • merged_A_DIA_step_export.tsv
Each boxplot corresponds to a 5 minute time interval and shows mean peak wifth and variation.Peak Width is calculated from the leftWidth and rightWidth columns. Alternativley, full widh at halfmaximum (fwhm) could also be used to represent this metric

ID over RT

This histogram shows the number of feature identified in a specified retention time interval. In this plot, each bar represents a 5 minute interval, the actual retention time is displayed in seconds on the x axis.
These plots can be generated from any OpenSwathWorkflow or pyprophet output files, that can be either in either in tsv or osw fromatFor each given input file a subplot is generated.
Please compare runs and make sure, the number of IDs are stable over RT dimension and between runs.
Files used to create plots:
  • FKL2872-S02-A-A_DIA_stepCE_1.osw
  • FKL2872-S10-A-A_DIA_stepCE_2.osw
  • FKL2872-S14-A-A_DIA_stepCE_3.osw
  • merged_A_DIA_step_export.tsv

Number of Transitions

Each feature has multiple transtions. to be precise, each has a count of 6, but since some the peaks are empty and will therefore not be counted. For tsv files, the number of available peaks can be counted from the column 'aggr_peak_area' is inspected. It contains a list of peaks and their respective masserrors. For osw files, number of transitions can be read from the table FEATURE_TRANSITION. it contains 6 transitions for each feature, but for some transitions, no peak was actually detected. So only each non zero AREA_INTENSITY (or alternatively APEX_INTENSITY) will be counted. The file from pyprophet contains all features and transitions from merged swath files, s o the total number will be much higher. But the number of features with only 1 - 3 transitions should go down considerably

Mean Mass Errors

This histogram shows the distribution of mean mass errors of each feature. The mean is calculated from the mass errors of all ions in a feature.
Careful; can only be plotted from swath tsv files

can only be plotted from swath TSV files

Missed Cleavages

For each sequence, OpenSwathWorkflow does an in situ digest (assuming Trypsin) and places the number of missed cleavages for each peptide in a column 'MC'. This columns can currently only be found in the tsv output from OpenSwathWorkflow, so this plot will only be available if swath tsv file(s) were provided.
Processing data: all peptides tagged as decoys are dropped before plotting and transitions groups are groupedso that each peptide is counted only once.
QC target: sample preparation

can only be plotted from swath TSV

RT correlation with library

Scatter plot of iRT against iRT difference, plotted from pyprophet output files

Coverage of Assay Library

Venn diagram of library coverage. This can only be plotted if the library assay list was provided in tsv format. Libraries in pqp format are currently not supported.
Library coverage will be plotted from tsv files, if they were provided, otherwise it can also be plotted from osw files.
Coverage of the merged file from pyprophet is inlcuded and will be plotted from tsv first, if bothe were provided.

no library file was provided

Library intensity correlation

The correlation of assay library (DDA) intensity with DIA intensity is calculated by OpenSwathWorkflow as one of many sub-scores, that describe describe the peak group. This score is plotted here as boxplot for each provided swath output file.
